Dreadful car accident in Svit

TWO persons were wounded, - including a child - as a result of a traffic accident which occurred on Saturday afternoon at approximately 5:20 p.m. in Svit. A 34- year-old driver from Košice was driving. The vehicle lost control while he was changing the CD and it collided with a electricity post.

40- year-old Jana Ondrušová of Trnavská police department confirmed to SITA that the accident occurred at a four-way stop at the end of the town. "The technician who was travelling with the woman in the accident is no longer alive. The woman remains in critical condition, she was brought by helicopter to a Košice hospital," Ondrušová said.
